WEBVTT

00:03.880 --> 00:05.670
[ Gunfire, explosions ]

00:05.670 --> 00:09.330
[ Breathing heavily,
grunting, gasps ]

00:09.330 --> 00:14.750
Owen:
As surgeons, we rely on cycles.

00:14.750 --> 00:16.380
Heartbeats.

00:16.380 --> 00:18.210
Cell regeneration.

00:18.210 --> 00:21.880
Circadian rhythms.

00:21.880 --> 00:25.170
We know something's wrong
when the cycle is broken.

00:25.170 --> 00:27.790
Our duty is to fix it.
[ Laughter ]

00:27.790 --> 00:29.500
To force the cogs
back in line.

00:29.500 --> 00:31.790
[ Laughter ]

00:31.790 --> 00:33.670
Sorry, sir!
Morning, sir!

00:33.670 --> 00:35.420
[ Helicopter blades whirring ]

00:35.420 --> 00:38.920
But that break can also be
useful, like a warning shot.

00:38.920 --> 00:40.540
[ Sighs ]

00:49.210 --> 00:51.380
Owen:
Beth, please. I know.

00:51.380 --> 00:54.080
Y-Yeah, my leave
was canceled. I --

00:54.080 --> 00:56.620
Don't cry. I will make this
up to you, I promise.

00:56.620 --> 00:57.960
She's got that vice grip
so tight,

00:57.960 --> 00:59.080
his testicles
are about to pop off.

00:59.080 --> 01:00.250
How you holding up?

01:00.250 --> 01:02.460
Well, considering
that today decides

01:02.460 --> 01:04.250
my entire military future?
Medium.

01:04.250 --> 01:05.750
You're a shoo-in.
[ Chuckles ]

01:05.750 --> 01:08.500
I think I'd rather focus on
my brother's pathetic love life.

01:08.500 --> 01:11.710
Hey, that was
an endearing conversation.
How's everything at home?

01:11.710 --> 01:13.500
All right. Let's focus on
getting this stuff loaded.

01:13.500 --> 01:15.040
We need to be in Fallujah
at 0700.

01:15.040 --> 01:16.670
I'd like to be
less uptight by 0700.

01:16.670 --> 01:19.580
Okay. Save it. The colonel's
coming. Where the hell is Riggs?

01:19.580 --> 01:22.830
He was on call last night.
I'll get him.

01:27.170 --> 01:30.120
Amelia:
[ Echoing ] Owen. Owen.

01:30.120 --> 01:32.460
Owen!

01:32.460 --> 01:34.170
Are you okay?

01:34.170 --> 01:36.250
Uh, yeah.
Yeah, I'm okay.

01:40.120 --> 01:42.670
It's --
It's not really goodbye.

01:42.670 --> 01:45.420
I mean, Los Angeles
is a two-hour flight,

01:45.420 --> 01:47.830
so you can see her
whenever you want.

01:47.830 --> 01:50.170
Yeah.

01:52.540 --> 01:54.540
How 'bout I make us
dinner tonight?

01:57.080 --> 01:58.960
Well, that
would be...nice.

01:58.960 --> 02:01.500
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

02:01.500 --> 02:03.710
[ Gasps ]
[ Phone clicks ]

02:03.710 --> 02:06.120
Hey! I'm getting
on the road now.

02:06.120 --> 02:07.210
Farouk:
How long till you're here?

02:07.210 --> 02:09.080
Uh, it's --
it's a long drive.

02:09.080 --> 02:11.830
Well, if you drive faster,
will you get here sooner?

02:11.830 --> 02:13.920
Just help Nathan
get everything ready,

02:13.920 --> 02:15.210
and you won't even
notice the time.

02:15.210 --> 02:16.830
[ Drill whirs ]
Aah! Son of a...

02:16.830 --> 02:17.920
Doubt it.

02:17.920 --> 02:19.290
Kisses, my sweet boy.

02:19.290 --> 02:21.210
Hey, will you give Nate
the phone?

02:22.710 --> 02:24.960
Oh. Thanks, buddy.

02:24.960 --> 02:27.000
Hey, baby,
how's it going?
How's he doing?

02:27.000 --> 02:29.330
[ Scoffs ] God. This has got to
be totally overwhelming for him.

02:29.330 --> 02:30.790
No, no, no. We're --
We're having a blast.

02:30.790 --> 02:32.040
And you got
his fan, right?

02:32.040 --> 02:33.960
I mean, he cannot sleep
without his fan.

02:33.960 --> 02:36.920
Uh, fan. Fan. Uh...

02:36.920 --> 02:39.790
Well, I'm not sure if...

02:39.790 --> 02:42.500
Oh, yeah. We got it.

02:42.500 --> 02:44.040
Okay.

02:44.040 --> 02:46.000
Now we just got to figure out
how to put it together.

02:48.960 --> 02:51.080
[ Door thuds ]
What was that?

02:52.380 --> 02:54.290
Uh, uh, I don't know.

02:54.290 --> 02:55.500
I didn't --
I didn't hear anything.

02:55.500 --> 02:56.750
Did you hear anything,
Farouk?

02:56.750 --> 02:58.210
The door falling!

02:58.210 --> 03:00.080
Shh. No. No, he didn't -- He
didn't hear anything, either.

03:00.080 --> 03:02.210
Mm-hmm.

03:02.210 --> 03:03.750
[ Door opens ]

03:06.120 --> 03:08.290
Megan: Incoming!
Aah!

03:08.290 --> 03:10.250
[ Laughing ]

03:12.420 --> 03:14.380
You're gonna kill me
one of these days.

03:14.380 --> 03:16.080
Oh, you love it.

03:19.790 --> 03:21.080
So, are we done fighting?

03:21.080 --> 03:22.880
You tell me.

03:24.880 --> 03:26.580
Come here.

03:28.710 --> 03:30.040
[ Megan laughs ]

03:30.040 --> 03:32.210
We're going to Fallujah.
Nathan: Hmm?

03:32.210 --> 03:33.380
We're going to Fallujah!

03:33.380 --> 03:34.500
Mnh-mnh.
Uh-huh.

03:34.500 --> 03:36.580
I prefer the relative
safety of Baghdad...

03:36.580 --> 03:38.670
and this bed.
[ Laughs ]

03:38.670 --> 03:41.790
No. No. I can't be late.
I can't be late. Not today.

03:41.790 --> 03:43.420
Oh, right. Your thing.

03:43.420 --> 03:46.960
The, um, the strack?
The strap? Strack?

03:46.960 --> 03:49.330
Strat!
As in stratification.

03:49.330 --> 03:51.460
As in if I don't get
ranked number one,

03:51.460 --> 03:53.920
I can kiss flight surgeon
goodbye, so...

04:05.380 --> 04:06.750
You weren't supposed to
find that.

04:10.120 --> 04:13.750
I know it's not exactly a ring,
but, as I recall,

04:13.750 --> 04:16.710
you -- you lost your class ring
in the surgical sink, so...

04:16.710 --> 04:18.000
Not a ring?

04:19.880 --> 04:22.120
Don't you dare do the thing,
unless you are doing the thing.

04:23.830 --> 04:25.580
Oh, my God. You are doing it.
[ Chuckles ]

04:25.580 --> 04:26.790
Megan Eloise Hunt,
will you --
Yes!!

04:26.790 --> 04:28.920
[ Laughs ]

04:28.920 --> 04:30.670
Yes. Yes.

04:34.580 --> 04:35.620
Let's go!

04:38.290 --> 04:39.830
Come on!
What kept you?!

04:39.830 --> 04:41.500
I said yes!

04:41.500 --> 04:42.830
-What?!
-Aah!

04:42.830 --> 04:44.670
And I asked her
to marry me!

04:44.670 --> 04:47.960
-Aah! Congratulations!
-About time!

04:47.960 --> 04:49.880
-Mwah!
-[ Laughs ]

04:49.880 --> 04:51.170
Oh, wait.
Look. Look, look.

04:51.170 --> 04:54.880
Wow! An engagement
necklace?

04:54.880 --> 04:57.040
Wow.
That's interesting.

04:57.040 --> 05:00.620
Yeah, well, she loses everything
that's not tied to her, so...

05:00.620 --> 05:03.000
[ Helicopter blades whirring ]

05:03.000 --> 05:05.580
[ Radio chatter ]

05:20.000 --> 05:22.380
Owen: Malibu -- it's too far
away, and it's too snooty.

05:22.380 --> 05:25.170
You're gonna hate it.
And Seattle has beaches.

05:25.170 --> 05:26.880
Freezing-cold beaches.
Not the same.

05:26.880 --> 05:28.710
[ Scoffs ]
Nathan found a job yet?

05:28.710 --> 05:30.290
He will.

05:30.290 --> 05:32.420
And if he doesn't, I'm sure
I could find some pole work.

05:32.420 --> 05:34.500
-[ Laughs ] Megan.
-I will come home for Christmas.

05:34.500 --> 05:36.170
And you'll come
visit me a lot,

05:36.170 --> 05:38.880
which will be so good
for you because, you know...

05:38.880 --> 05:41.080
the sun.
[ Laughter ]

05:44.000 --> 05:45.580
I'll miss you, Eeyore.

05:45.580 --> 05:47.290
[ Chuckles ]

05:47.290 --> 05:48.790
Come here.

05:51.710 --> 05:53.210
-Okay.
-Okay.

05:55.380 --> 05:56.920
Bye.

05:56.920 --> 05:59.960
[ Door opens and closes ]

05:59.960 --> 06:01.540
Colonel's convoy inbound.

06:01.540 --> 06:03.960
Owen: All right, gents.
Chins up, backs straight.

06:03.960 --> 06:06.250
Stand with dignity,
not sloppiness.

06:06.250 --> 06:07.710
I'm talking to you,
Sergeant!

06:07.710 --> 06:09.290
Yes, sir,
Major Diamond, sir!

06:09.290 --> 06:11.790
Matthews: I just don't
want to be ranked last.

06:11.790 --> 06:13.330
Tubs failed his PT test.
He's last.

06:13.330 --> 06:15.210
We're all gunning
for second place anyway.

06:15.210 --> 06:16.790
You know Hunt's stratted
number one.

06:16.790 --> 06:18.170
The best will be first,
so, yeah, you're right.

06:18.170 --> 06:19.670
Wish my brother
was the C.O.

06:19.670 --> 06:21.080
Your mom could be C.O.
and you'd still be last.

06:21.080 --> 06:22.210
[ Stifled laughter ]

06:23.830 --> 06:25.170
Owen: At-ten-hut!

06:31.920 --> 06:33.290
[ Vehicle door closes ]

06:36.880 --> 06:38.420
At ease.

06:40.080 --> 06:41.290
Excellent work,
Major Hunt.

06:41.290 --> 06:43.500
Before I get started
on this tour,

06:43.500 --> 06:45.880
let's get to what
you all really want to know --

06:45.880 --> 06:47.170
my strat rankings.

06:47.170 --> 06:49.250
It was a difficult decision,

06:49.250 --> 06:51.290
but join me in congratulating
Lieutenant John Matthews.

06:53.580 --> 06:55.620
[ Applause ]

06:55.620 --> 07:01.670
♪♪

07:01.670 --> 07:03.830
Man: Talon 1 to Sparrow. We have
an emergency inbound. Copy?

07:03.830 --> 07:05.670
Talon 1, copy that.

07:05.670 --> 07:07.750
Marine FOB Ace Hole
reports two active shooters.

07:07.750 --> 07:09.920
We have four KIA and
20 wounded headed your way.

07:09.920 --> 07:11.380
Copy that.
We'll be ready. Out.

07:11.380 --> 07:14.830
All surgeons on deck!
Frontload supplies! Fall out!

07:14.830 --> 07:22.710
♪♪

07:26.920 --> 07:28.540
-What are you doing?
-I'm coming with you.

07:28.540 --> 07:30.080
[ Laughs ] What?

07:30.080 --> 07:31.330
Road trip.

07:31.330 --> 07:33.330
[ Laughs ]
Are you serious?

07:33.330 --> 07:35.880
You said you wanted
to beat traffic.

07:35.880 --> 07:37.880
What are you waiting for?
Drive!

07:37.880 --> 07:39.620
[ Engine starts ]

07:39.620 --> 07:41.120
[ Both chuckle ]

07:51.290 --> 07:52.920
Are you sure about this? I can
just drop you at the corner.

07:52.920 --> 07:54.290
Shut up.
I love road trips.
Since when?

07:54.290 --> 07:55.620
Since we were kids.
Roadtripping with Mom and Dad.

07:55.620 --> 07:57.420
You used to hate
those trips!

07:57.420 --> 07:59.040
We -- We would fight
so much

07:59.040 --> 08:01.420
that Mom and Dad would threaten
to leave us at a gas station.

08:01.420 --> 08:03.330
Well, fortunately,
we're grown-ups now.

08:03.330 --> 08:04.500
How do you work
this radio?

08:04.500 --> 08:07.120
I'm just saying...
I don't need a babysitter.

08:07.120 --> 08:08.790
I am not a babysitter,
I'm a copilot.

08:08.790 --> 08:10.960
[ Music plays on radio ]
Here to ensure
you don't fall asleep,

08:10.960 --> 08:12.460
swerve off a cliff
to a fiery death.

08:12.460 --> 08:14.830
We're driving straight through.
No detours.

08:14.830 --> 08:17.120
Whatever you say.
I'm just along for the ride.

08:17.120 --> 08:19.710
[ Breathes deeply ]

08:19.710 --> 08:21.880
♪♪

08:21.880 --> 08:23.380
Superficial laceration.

08:23.380 --> 08:24.920
See that nurse over there
for steri-strips.

08:24.920 --> 08:27.380
Matthews is top strat?
What the hell happened?

08:27.380 --> 08:29.330
The Colonel has
the final say. Go.
How hard did you push?

08:29.330 --> 08:30.710
Did you tell him that
I was CGO of the year?

08:30.710 --> 08:33.290
Of course! You know how
political these things are.

08:33.290 --> 08:35.580
I'm never gonna get
flight-surgeon training now.

08:35.580 --> 08:38.000
Okay, let's go.
Come on, guys!
Come on through!

08:38.000 --> 08:42.040
PFC Tyler Budreaux.
Pulse 90s, BP 100s over 50s.

08:42.040 --> 08:45.330
I'd salute you, sir,
but I can't feel my arm.

08:45.330 --> 08:46.500
What happened out there?

08:46.500 --> 08:48.330
Two of the Iraqi allies
went rogue. Opened fire.

08:48.330 --> 08:50.080
Tyler pushed people
out of the way.

08:50.080 --> 08:51.290
You're looking at a
freakin' American hero, sir.

08:51.290 --> 08:52.880
I really do need
my arm, sir.

08:52.880 --> 08:54.380
We're gonna do
everything we can.

08:54.380 --> 08:56.330
Hang two grams of cefazolin
and get him prepped for the O.R.

08:56.330 --> 08:58.670
[ Woman yelling in Arabic ]

08:58.670 --> 09:00.920
Stop! Stop! She doesn't --
Wait! Stop!

09:00.920 --> 09:02.790
Don't touch her! She doesn't
want to be touched by men!

09:02.790 --> 09:04.170
Hey, listen.
I got this. You go.

09:06.960 --> 09:08.750
Hey, hey, I got it. Here.
Get out of the way.

09:08.750 --> 09:11.000
"GSW upper right chest.
Diminished breathing sounds."

09:11.000 --> 09:12.210
She needs a chest tube.

09:12.210 --> 09:14.080
[ Moaning ]

09:14.080 --> 09:18.210
[ Speaking Arabic ]

09:18.210 --> 09:19.880
All right.
Let me take a look.

09:19.880 --> 09:22.290
-Where do you want him?
-Shrapnel wound. Pre-op.

09:22.290 --> 09:24.420
What do we have?

09:24.420 --> 09:27.540
MP: Nadir al-Jabouri.
Multiple GSWs to the torso.

09:27.540 --> 09:28.960
Perp believed to be
the second shooter.

09:28.960 --> 09:30.120
And he's still alive?

09:30.120 --> 09:32.290
Unfortunately.
You treat that woman well.

09:32.290 --> 09:33.830
'Cause she saved
everyone's ass!

09:33.830 --> 09:36.120
Tried to wrestle
his gun from him.

09:36.120 --> 09:39.620
He needs an ex lap.
O.R. ASAP. Let's go.

09:39.620 --> 09:42.000
Nathan, scrub in with me?
-You got it.

09:42.000 --> 09:43.710
Let's go! Let's go!

09:43.710 --> 09:45.460
[ Waves crashing ]

09:45.460 --> 09:47.040
We'll make your bed
a racecar,

09:47.040 --> 09:48.880
so you can go really fast
in your dreams.

09:48.880 --> 09:50.420
[ Chuckles ]
A race car?

09:50.420 --> 09:53.120
Yeah, you know,
like NASCAR or Formula 1?

09:53.120 --> 09:55.710
It's a car that goes
really, really fast.

09:55.710 --> 09:57.750
-My bed?
-Trust me, it's cool.

09:57.750 --> 10:00.500
Then where will
Mama sleep?

10:00.500 --> 10:03.460
Well, in her room. Our room.
It's just across the hall.

10:03.460 --> 10:06.620
But back home, we used to
sleep in the same room.

10:06.620 --> 10:08.120
It's safer that way.

10:08.120 --> 10:09.880
This is home now,
buddy.

10:09.880 --> 10:12.620
[ Sighs ]

10:12.620 --> 10:14.670
Hey, I know
it's an adjustment, okay?

10:14.670 --> 10:16.580
But once you start school,
you're gonna feel settled.

10:16.580 --> 10:17.960
Mama has always been
my teacher

10:17.960 --> 10:19.830
Well, now she
won't need to be.

10:19.830 --> 10:22.040
You're gonna get to go
to school with a bunch
of kids your own age.

10:22.040 --> 10:24.000
You're gonna make
lots of friends.

10:24.000 --> 10:26.290
Maybe join the band, you know?
You can play sports.

10:26.290 --> 10:27.960
Soccer, baseball.
You're gonna love it.

10:27.960 --> 10:29.000
[ Bulb shatters ]

10:29.000 --> 10:31.710
I'm sorry! So sorry!

10:31.710 --> 10:34.290
It's okay. It's okay. But
you got bare feet. Hang on.

10:34.290 --> 10:36.080
There you go.
You're all right.

10:37.790 --> 10:39.080
[ Bulb pieces rattling ]

10:40.880 --> 10:43.120
See? Not a problem.

10:44.580 --> 10:46.750
[ Indistinct conversations,
monitors beeping ]

10:53.420 --> 10:54.880
Teddy: That really is

10:54.880 --> 10:57.380
a beautiful necklace
that you got for Megan.

10:57.380 --> 11:00.210
Where'd you find
emeralds in Baghdad?

11:00.210 --> 11:01.750
You want one
for yourself?

11:01.750 --> 11:03.250
You seem awfully stuck
on it.

11:03.250 --> 11:04.960
It just reminds me
so much of the necklace

11:04.960 --> 11:07.790
that Sergeant Philips got
from her boyfriend back home.

11:07.790 --> 11:09.000
You know...

11:09.000 --> 11:10.790
Felicia Philips?

11:10.790 --> 11:15.210
Well, but hers in engraved
with her initials on the back.

11:15.210 --> 11:16.830
It's engraved?

11:16.830 --> 11:18.750
Yep.

11:18.750 --> 11:20.040
Ten blade.

11:23.170 --> 11:25.170
♪ Can't you hear
that music pumpin' hard ♪

11:25.170 --> 11:26.500
♪ Like I wish you would? ♪

11:26.500 --> 11:27.790
♪ Now push it ♪

11:27.790 --> 11:29.790
♪ Ner, ner-ner,
ner-ner, enh ♪

11:29.790 --> 11:30.960
♪ Push it good! ♪

11:33.000 --> 11:34.750
♪ P-Push it real good! ♪

11:34.750 --> 11:37.330
[ Laughter ]

11:37.330 --> 11:38.380
Hey, open these for me,
will ya?

11:38.380 --> 11:40.540
Ew! No.

11:40.540 --> 11:42.000
What?
There's no food
in that food.

11:42.000 --> 11:44.080
I'm starving!
You can eat next time
we stop for gas.

11:44.080 --> 11:46.750
♪♪

11:46.750 --> 11:49.120
[ Laughs ]

11:49.120 --> 11:51.670
♪ Get up on this ♪

11:51.670 --> 11:54.290
GPS: Please return
to the highlighted route.

11:54.290 --> 11:56.330
Uh, what she said.

11:56.330 --> 11:58.170
Shortcut.

11:58.170 --> 12:00.120
To what? The place where
unsuspecting teenagers

12:00.120 --> 12:01.670
get picked off
one by one?

12:01.670 --> 12:03.380
Come on.
Don't you trust me?

12:03.380 --> 12:06.290
♪ You really got me going,
you got me so ♪

12:06.290 --> 12:07.620
Fine.

12:07.620 --> 12:08.920
♪ I don't know what I'm doing ♪

12:18.210 --> 12:19.710
On the one hand,
I could hug you.

12:19.710 --> 12:20.960
On the other hand...

12:20.960 --> 12:22.290
[ Hushed ]
I'm scared.

12:22.290 --> 12:24.170
[ Chuckles ] Yeah.
You used to love this place.

12:24.170 --> 12:25.750
Uh, that was before
it was haunted.

12:25.750 --> 12:28.380
You know, I just thought
you'd want a ring-toss rematch,

12:28.380 --> 12:31.880
since you used to always lose
and cry and say that I cheated.

12:31.880 --> 12:33.750
Uh, you did cheat.

12:33.750 --> 12:35.120
Whatever helps you sleep
at night.

12:35.120 --> 12:36.420
One game.

12:36.420 --> 12:38.330
Okay. [ Chuckles ]

12:38.330 --> 12:39.540
Okay. Oh, my gosh.

12:39.540 --> 12:41.330
This brings back
so many memories!

12:41.330 --> 12:44.080
[ Laughs ]

12:44.080 --> 12:45.880
Okay, it's over here.

12:45.880 --> 12:47.750
Oh, remember this?
No? Okay.

12:47.750 --> 12:49.670
[ Laughter ]

12:51.460 --> 12:54.540
[ Speaking Arabic ]

12:54.540 --> 12:56.670
No. I don't want
to undress.

12:56.670 --> 12:58.250
I hate to be naked
in front of strangers, too,

12:58.250 --> 12:59.920
but I can't help you
if you don't let me.

13:03.040 --> 13:04.920
My name is Megan.
What's yours?

13:10.330 --> 13:14.000
Sana.
It's -- It's Sana.

13:14.000 --> 13:16.330
Sana.
[ Groans ]

13:18.710 --> 13:21.330
It doesn't look too bad. Go
ahead and place a chest tube.

13:21.330 --> 13:22.920
[ Wheezing ]

13:22.920 --> 13:26.380
[ Speaking Arabic ]

13:26.380 --> 13:28.500
Hey, you were --
you were great with her.

13:28.500 --> 13:31.960
Yeah, right? It's almost like
I know how to do my job.

13:31.960 --> 13:33.920
Hey, uh...

13:33.920 --> 13:35.580
How about you scrub in
on my mangled arm?

13:35.580 --> 13:36.920
Oh, God. Don't.

13:36.920 --> 13:38.960
Don't what?
My dream was just crushed.

13:38.960 --> 13:40.210
A pity party
isn't going to fix it.

13:40.210 --> 13:41.830
I-I just figured
it'd be nice to talk,

13:41.830 --> 13:43.420
you know, celebrate
the good things in life,

13:43.420 --> 13:45.670
which still exist,
despite the strat.

13:45.670 --> 13:47.620
Like, how Mom's head's gonna
explode planning two weddings.

13:47.620 --> 13:49.250
Two weddings?
Come on.

13:49.250 --> 13:52.080
Maybe Mom can plan your divorce
while she's at it.

13:52.080 --> 13:54.670
Nathan: You're gonna need
more packing in the
left upper quadrant.

13:54.670 --> 13:56.920
This spleen is shattered.
More lap pads!

13:56.920 --> 13:59.290
Of all the stupid,
selfish, moronic,

13:59.290 --> 14:01.170
and completely
preventable --

14:01.170 --> 14:04.170
Okay, this is not our place to
judge, Dr. Altman, just repair.

14:04.170 --> 14:05.500
I'm not talking about him.

14:05.500 --> 14:07.540
[ Monitor beeping ]

14:10.330 --> 14:11.880
You don't know
the whole story.

14:11.880 --> 14:14.460
Teddy: He opened fire on the
people he loved, who loved him.

14:14.460 --> 14:15.710
That's betrayal.

14:15.710 --> 14:17.750
And no amount of rationalization
makes it okay.

14:17.750 --> 14:19.170
Suction!

14:19.170 --> 14:20.290
[ Suction ]

14:21.540 --> 14:22.960
Nathan:
No, that's an --

14:22.960 --> 14:24.670
No, that's an
entry-level position.

14:24.670 --> 14:27.670
I have both field experience
and NGO lead work.

14:27.670 --> 14:30.380
Excuse me. I need this one.
I'm not sure what you call it.

14:30.380 --> 14:31.620
Okay, that's
a screwdriver, buddy.

14:31.620 --> 14:33.170
Well, you're gonna
have to do better.

14:33.170 --> 14:34.960
I can't find this
in the tools.

14:34.960 --> 14:36.380
Yeah? Well, uh-huh.

14:36.380 --> 14:37.710
Well, that can't be
all the local hospitals.

14:37.710 --> 14:39.420
And I'm not gonna take
less than what I'm worth.

14:39.420 --> 14:41.380
Why am I paying you a commission
if you're not getting me

14:41.380 --> 14:43.040
what it is that
I'm expecting you to get?

14:43.040 --> 14:45.420
-But --
-Yes.

14:45.420 --> 14:48.420
-Ah, lucky shot. Lucky.
-Boom!

14:48.420 --> 14:50.120
I just hooked
a tetanus-riddled ring

14:50.120 --> 14:51.380
around the last bottle
standing.

14:51.380 --> 14:54.170
-That's not luck.
-Mm-hmm. Okay.

14:54.170 --> 14:55.620
Uh, I get this,

14:55.620 --> 14:57.420
and I control the music
for the rest of the trip.

14:57.420 --> 14:59.080
Uh, that's a lot
of Kenny Loggins.

14:59.080 --> 15:00.330
Miss, miss, miss, miss!

15:00.330 --> 15:02.460
-Ugh!
-Oh! [ Laughs ]

15:02.460 --> 15:04.380
Okay, um,
if I make this,

15:04.380 --> 15:07.210
you have to wear ugly sweaters
for all of Christmas.

15:07.210 --> 15:08.960
Okay. [ Laughs ]

15:08.960 --> 15:11.210
-Ugh!
-Phew.

15:11.210 --> 15:14.380
Uh, okay.
I get this and...

15:14.380 --> 15:15.830
you stay in Seattle.

15:15.830 --> 15:17.880
Yeah.

15:19.710 --> 15:22.120
Yes! Mm!

15:22.120 --> 15:24.540
Okay, looks like we
have to turn around now.

15:24.540 --> 15:26.540
[ Chuckles ]

15:26.540 --> 15:27.880
Unbelievable.

15:27.880 --> 15:29.580
Megan, I'm kidding.

15:29.580 --> 15:31.120
You're not kidding. This is
the whole reason you came.

15:31.120 --> 15:32.290
You're blowing this
out of proportion.

15:32.290 --> 15:33.620
You think you know
what's best for me,

15:33.620 --> 15:36.000
ever since we were kids,
whether it's what I want or not.

15:36.000 --> 15:38.000
Lifeguarding?
You're not a good swimmer.

15:38.000 --> 15:40.330
Serving.
Excuse me for not wanting
my sister to get shot at.

15:40.330 --> 15:42.040
My strat!
Your strat?!

15:42.040 --> 15:44.460
You still playing dumb
about it?

15:44.460 --> 15:45.710
That was 10 years ago,
Megan!

15:45.710 --> 15:48.620
And I got kidnapped before
we could fight about it!

15:52.670 --> 15:54.750
[ Monitor beeping ]

15:57.250 --> 15:59.920
Megan: 2-0 silk tie.

15:59.920 --> 16:01.540
So it's settled.

16:01.540 --> 16:03.210
Tonight you'll call Beth
and tell her that you're done.

16:03.210 --> 16:04.880
One less wedding
for Mom to worry about.

16:04.880 --> 16:07.620
[ Scoffs ]
it's not that simple, Megan.

16:07.620 --> 16:08.960
Okay, maybe
it's that simple.

16:08.960 --> 16:10.880
You know I'm right.

16:10.880 --> 16:13.000
We'll see. Scissors.

16:17.790 --> 16:20.330
You know, I was gonna miss
this -- working together.

16:20.330 --> 16:22.920
Your flight-surgeon training
was gonna tie you up for months.

16:22.920 --> 16:24.330
And for what?

16:24.330 --> 16:26.750
Tying tourniquets
with Special Forces

16:26.750 --> 16:29.040
somewhere three times
as dangerous as here.

16:29.040 --> 16:31.380
Ask me,
you dodged a bullet.

16:31.380 --> 16:33.170
You recommended me,
didn't you?

16:34.620 --> 16:36.250
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]

16:36.250 --> 16:38.830
He's lost more blood
than we thought. Let's
get him stabilized.

16:42.460 --> 16:43.880
You know
it wasn't my decision.

16:47.620 --> 16:49.750
Carnival?
That sounds fun.

16:49.750 --> 16:52.880
Or maybe not.

16:52.880 --> 16:55.750
All right, well, we'll be here
with the lights on, babe.

16:55.750 --> 16:58.250
Drive safe.

16:58.250 --> 16:59.750
Hey, Farouk, Megan's
gonna be a little late,

16:59.750 --> 17:01.830
but I got good news!

17:01.830 --> 17:03.580
Found your screwdriver.

17:03.580 --> 17:05.210
Farouk?

17:07.620 --> 17:09.170
Hey, buddy?

17:11.670 --> 17:12.960
Farouk!

17:16.120 --> 17:18.290
Hey! Farouk!

17:25.170 --> 17:28.120
Farouk!

17:28.120 --> 17:30.790
Hey, hey! Have you guys
seen a little boy go by?
About 10 years old?

17:32.040 --> 17:33.710
We need to pack, shunt,
and get out of here.

17:33.710 --> 17:35.540
No. I want to do a reversed
saphenous vein graft.

17:35.540 --> 17:37.040
Not with these vitals.
The best we can do

17:37.040 --> 17:39.500
is get the limb perfused
and get him stabilized.

17:39.500 --> 17:41.540
The graft will take too long,
and it's too risky.

17:41.540 --> 17:42.790
I know you don't think
that I'm qualified.

17:42.790 --> 17:44.290
But this is the right call.
He wants to save the arm.

17:44.290 --> 17:46.000
Not at the expense
of his life.

17:46.000 --> 17:48.500
I am more experienced.
I outrank you.

17:48.500 --> 17:51.210
So, we're gonna do things my --
Megan, what the hell?!

17:51.210 --> 17:52.040
Betadine!

17:54.250 --> 17:55.380
[ Sighs ]

18:05.790 --> 18:08.000
Well, you have to stop
for food at some point.
Not hungry.

18:09.670 --> 18:12.540
[ Cellphone rings ]

18:12.540 --> 18:14.540
Hey.

18:14.540 --> 18:16.580
Yeah. It's fine.
Uh, what's up?

18:16.580 --> 18:18.710
Just checking what time
you'll be home for dinner.

18:18.710 --> 18:20.210
I'm sorry.

18:20.210 --> 18:23.000
I-I decided to drive with Megan,
and I completely forgot to call.

18:23.000 --> 18:24.750
I-I didn't want her
driving alone.

18:24.750 --> 18:28.080
So...

18:28.080 --> 18:30.790
We're having a blast.

18:30.790 --> 18:33.710
Yeah.

18:33.710 --> 18:35.580
Okay. Bye.

18:38.080 --> 18:40.040
Are there any women in your life
you don't lie to?

18:43.500 --> 18:46.500
[ Radio button clicks ]
♪ You've got to know
when to hold 'em ♪

18:46.500 --> 18:49.540
♪ Know when to fold 'em ♪

18:49.540 --> 18:52.620
♪ Know when to walk away
and know... ♪

18:52.620 --> 18:54.620
[ Panting ]

19:01.880 --> 19:03.580
[ Indistinct conversations ]

19:05.920 --> 19:07.210
Excuse me.

19:10.960 --> 19:14.500
Farouk. Buddy.

19:14.500 --> 19:16.830
You can't just
run off like that.

19:16.830 --> 19:18.500
You had me terrified.

19:21.620 --> 19:22.920
Is everything okay?

19:22.920 --> 19:25.040
You were very busy.
I thought I could help.

19:25.040 --> 19:26.790
I thought I could
get us some food,

19:26.790 --> 19:30.670
but there's
just so many choices!

19:35.710 --> 19:37.170
[ Sighs ]

19:42.170 --> 19:43.620
Yeah.

19:43.620 --> 19:46.330
[ Monitor beeping ]

19:46.330 --> 19:48.040
Nathan: Okay. Bleeding's
controlled over here. Clip.

19:48.040 --> 19:49.540
Teddy: Yep, same here.
Irrigation.

19:54.080 --> 19:56.620
Say he regrets it.
Pardon?

19:56.620 --> 19:59.790
He made a huge mistake. He hurt
the people he cares about most.

19:59.790 --> 20:01.210
But say he regrets it.

20:01.210 --> 20:03.750
He was scared,
stupid, and wrong,

20:03.750 --> 20:05.580
and now he can feel
everything slipping away

20:05.580 --> 20:07.790
and he'll do anything he can
to make it right again.

20:07.790 --> 20:10.210
I'd say too bad
he didn't think about that

20:10.210 --> 20:11.670
before pulling the trigger.

20:15.460 --> 20:18.580
He's still hypotensive.
We need to cut our losses
and get out of here!

20:18.580 --> 20:21.250
Start the pressors. Would
you stop being so dramatic
and help me sew?

20:21.250 --> 20:23.210
Well, stop being so pig-headed
and listen to me sometimes!

20:23.210 --> 20:25.080
Shut up! Please. Sir.

20:27.460 --> 20:28.670
I'm almost there.

20:33.790 --> 20:35.170
Clamps off.

20:46.920 --> 20:48.670
He gets to keep his arm
and his life.

20:48.670 --> 20:50.830
-Yeah!
-Whoo!

20:50.830 --> 20:52.580
That was...impressive.

20:52.580 --> 20:55.290
I wish it didn't come
as such a surprise.

20:55.290 --> 20:57.170
You can finish the rest.

21:01.000 --> 21:02.880
[ Sighs ]

21:04.920 --> 21:07.540
I put thousands of hours in
to become the best.

21:07.540 --> 21:09.710
The best at central lines.
The best at one-handed ties.

21:09.710 --> 21:13.420
The best military officer.
I had my entire career planned.

21:13.420 --> 21:15.380
I was gonna attach to Special
Forces and become a general.

21:15.380 --> 21:17.040
Your qualifications
were not up for debate.

21:17.040 --> 21:19.250
So you had to convince them
that I was wrong for the job?

21:19.250 --> 21:21.710
All I had to do was tell them
the truth. That you're a child.

21:21.710 --> 21:24.670
[ Scoffs ]
That you make rash,
reckless decisions,

21:24.670 --> 21:26.880
and you never learn better
because I'm always there
to bail you out!

21:26.880 --> 21:28.210
If you'd gone
with Special Forces,

21:28.210 --> 21:29.420
you wouldn't have
made general.

21:29.420 --> 21:31.120
You'd have been dead
in under a month!

21:31.120 --> 21:33.080
And 10 years later,
what have you learned? Nothing.

21:33.080 --> 21:34.250
You're running
from your family.

21:34.250 --> 21:36.000
You're running from
your support system.

21:36.000 --> 21:37.380
And why?
Because you like the beach?!

21:37.380 --> 21:40.040
That's not a plan, Megan.
That's a whim.

21:40.040 --> 21:42.580
So, yes,
I tanked your strat.

21:42.580 --> 21:45.290
If I had to do it over,
I would do the same damn thing!

21:56.460 --> 21:58.420
[ Sea gulls cry ]

22:05.290 --> 22:07.380
So -- So, you're just gonna
punish me like you always do

22:07.380 --> 22:09.080
when I tell you
something you don't like.

22:11.040 --> 22:12.580
Fine.

22:12.580 --> 22:14.210
But you can't think of
anything to say

22:14.210 --> 22:15.330
because you know
that I'm right.

22:15.330 --> 22:16.880
And, for the record,

22:16.880 --> 22:20.120
this is the childish behavior
I was talking about.

22:20.120 --> 22:21.880
Diamond.
Excuse me?

22:21.880 --> 22:24.580
Your nickname.
In Baghdad. Remember?

22:24.580 --> 22:26.420
Major Diamond.

22:26.420 --> 22:27.880
Yes.

22:27.880 --> 22:29.670
Know why they
called you that?

22:29.670 --> 22:33.420
Well, they told me --
sharp, clear, focused.

22:33.420 --> 22:36.080
Anal-retentive.
High-strung.

22:36.080 --> 22:39.290
So uptight that if you
put coal in your ass,

22:39.290 --> 22:40.790
a diamond would pop out.

22:42.880 --> 22:44.460
You thought
it was a compliment.

22:44.460 --> 22:46.880
Which only
made it funnier.

22:46.880 --> 22:48.170
[ Chuckles ]
[ Laughs ]

22:48.170 --> 22:51.120
Like I said. A child.

22:51.120 --> 22:52.790
And, for the record,
I came up with it.

22:54.960 --> 22:56.460
Sorry I never told you,

22:56.460 --> 22:58.290
but, you know,
since we're coming clean.

23:04.580 --> 23:06.960
More choices!
Yeah, but it's not
always a bad thing.

23:06.960 --> 23:09.000
I mean, just try
a little of each

23:09.000 --> 23:11.170
and see which ones
you like.

23:20.920 --> 23:22.580
You dig?
Yeah.

23:26.460 --> 23:28.960
Can you keep a secret?

23:28.960 --> 23:33.210
I'm a little terrified
about starting over down here.

23:33.210 --> 23:36.460
In a new town.
New family.

23:36.460 --> 23:38.790
I don't even have a job,
and I want everything
to be perfect for Megan,

23:38.790 --> 23:40.460
but it took me half a day
to put a door on.

23:42.880 --> 23:45.500
So...what will you do?

23:45.500 --> 23:49.330
Well...

23:49.330 --> 23:51.170
I guess I'm gonna
have to be okay

23:51.170 --> 23:53.880
with not knowing
all the answers.

23:53.880 --> 23:55.420
You know,
count on the fact

23:55.420 --> 23:58.420
that we love Megan
and she loves us

23:58.420 --> 24:01.080
and just trust that together,
the three of us,

24:01.080 --> 24:03.250
we can figure
this thing out.

24:10.080 --> 24:11.620
Can you teach me
baseball?

24:11.620 --> 24:13.710
Yeah, sure.
I can teach you baseball.

24:13.710 --> 24:16.460
As soon as I learn
how to play.

24:16.460 --> 24:19.080
[ Both laugh ]

24:22.710 --> 24:23.920
Nathan: That's all
we can do for now.

24:23.920 --> 24:25.500
He'll make transport.

24:25.500 --> 24:27.170
And if he's lucky,
they'll fly him to Baghdad.

24:27.170 --> 24:28.330
Yeah. If he's lucky.

24:33.750 --> 24:35.250
How could you
do this to her?

24:35.250 --> 24:37.120
I don't know.
We were fighting...

24:37.120 --> 24:39.420
You were fighting,
so you proposed to her

24:39.420 --> 24:41.790
with your side piece's
stolen property?

24:41.790 --> 24:43.790
No. Look.
Felicia's not --

24:43.790 --> 24:45.080
It was a one-time thing.

24:47.120 --> 24:48.710
What am I gonna do,
Teddy?

24:51.000 --> 24:53.120
Did you mean it?
The proposal?

24:53.120 --> 24:56.250
Of course.
Look. Megan --

24:56.250 --> 24:57.790
Okay, we fight.
But she's the one.

24:57.790 --> 24:59.540
Okay? I was gonna tell her
about Felicia.

24:59.540 --> 25:01.500
I was gonna come clean.
And then she found the necklace.

25:01.500 --> 25:03.250
And I -- I panicked.

25:03.250 --> 25:05.330
-Well, she's gonna find out.
-I know.

25:05.330 --> 25:07.580
And if it comes from
anyone but you --
I know.

25:07.580 --> 25:08.920
Well, so...

25:08.920 --> 25:10.290
you have your answer.

25:12.120 --> 25:14.330
Well, you think
there's a chance?

25:16.710 --> 25:19.120
Well, she's got a temper,

25:19.120 --> 25:20.920
and she has every right
to be angry.

25:20.920 --> 25:23.580
And when Owen finds out,
he is gonna snap your neck.
Yeah.

25:23.580 --> 25:26.420
But...

25:26.420 --> 25:28.710
people mess up.

25:28.710 --> 25:30.380
And people forgive.

25:32.750 --> 25:35.620
It's what most pop songs and
most modern literature is about,

25:35.620 --> 25:37.710
so, yes, Nathan...

25:37.710 --> 25:40.540
tell her the truth,
and there's a chance.

25:58.420 --> 26:00.750
It was wrong of me to get in
the way of your career.

26:00.750 --> 26:04.830
It was none of my business.
I was out of line.

26:04.830 --> 26:07.330
It was just -- just wrong.
And I'm sorry.

26:08.580 --> 26:10.000
Thank you.

26:14.000 --> 26:16.000
But it doesn't change
the fact that Seattle
schools are excellent.

26:16.000 --> 26:17.500
Oh, my God!
Give it a rest!

26:17.500 --> 26:19.750
Nathan already has a job there,
plus it's safer, familiar.

26:19.750 --> 26:21.420
Closer to family.

26:21.420 --> 26:22.580
[ Horn blares ]
Whoa. What are you doing?

26:24.330 --> 26:26.920
Get out!
Get out of my car, Owen!

26:26.920 --> 26:28.380
[ Chuckles ]
Stop being ridiculous.

26:28.380 --> 26:31.170
No! Get out!
Stop it!

26:31.170 --> 26:32.580
Owen: What do you mean,
Megan's not coming?

26:32.580 --> 26:34.670
Well, she thinks you tanked
her strat. She's mad.

26:34.670 --> 26:36.380
Well, I hope you told her
she was crazy.

26:36.380 --> 26:39.250
Is she?
Oh, great. Not you, too?

26:39.250 --> 26:41.170
I'm just asking.
I'm not accusing.

26:41.170 --> 26:42.710
You know what?
She got engaged.

26:42.710 --> 26:45.460
You'd think she'd want to
live a safe, happy life.

26:45.460 --> 26:47.330
Plan a wedding, maybe.
Is that such a crazy thought?

26:47.330 --> 26:50.460
God! She wanted
that strat, Owen.

26:50.460 --> 26:52.250
It's all she thinks about.
And she was so close.

26:52.250 --> 26:54.120
Do you know how hard it is
to stand by

26:54.120 --> 26:56.380
and watch someone else
live the life that you want?

26:56.380 --> 26:59.250
The life that you're willing
to give up everything for?

26:59.250 --> 27:00.790
You're an idiot!

27:00.790 --> 27:03.000
Major,
we need to head out!

27:05.330 --> 27:07.290
Owen: Well, make sure Megan
rides back with you guys.

27:07.290 --> 27:09.460
I can only tolerate
so many tantrums.

27:09.460 --> 27:12.250
[ Helicopter blades whirring ]

27:16.960 --> 27:20.080
[ Radio chatter ]

27:27.580 --> 27:28.670
Megan: Get out!

27:30.670 --> 27:32.080
Get out! I mean it!

27:32.080 --> 27:33.750
Stop this.
No.

27:33.750 --> 27:35.380
If you can't support me,
then you can hitchhike.

27:35.380 --> 27:36.920
-Because I am done. Get out!
-Stop it!

27:36.920 --> 27:37.920
I'm not leaving you again!

27:42.040 --> 27:44.460
You have to stop
doing this.

27:44.460 --> 27:46.960
You -- You can't keep making
decisions for me, Owen.

27:46.960 --> 27:48.380
'Cause you are making
a bad decision.

27:48.380 --> 27:50.000
You are the only one
who thinks that.

27:50.000 --> 27:51.790
Nathan's the reason
we lost you in the first place.

27:51.790 --> 27:53.210
You don't know what
you're talking about!

27:53.210 --> 27:54.960
He cheated on you and now you're
starting a family with him?

27:54.960 --> 27:57.040
And you cheated
on your first wife.

27:57.040 --> 27:58.620
Mom told me all about it.

27:58.620 --> 28:01.250
And don't even get me started
on you and Teddy.

28:01.250 --> 28:04.080
So spare me the
"holier than thou" crap.

28:04.080 --> 28:06.210
You cheated, Nathan cheated.
It happens.

28:06.210 --> 28:09.710
Life happens.
People are imperfect.

28:09.710 --> 28:13.830
We fail and we fall, and some of
us get kidnapped for a decade,

28:13.830 --> 28:15.460
and when we get a second chance
at life and happiness,

28:15.460 --> 28:17.960
we seize it,
regardless of who cheated!

28:17.960 --> 28:19.790
Because now we know
what matters.

28:19.790 --> 28:21.750
Because now we know
what's precious.

28:21.750 --> 28:22.960
Because now we know that

28:22.960 --> 28:24.620
any tiny little moment
of happiness

28:24.620 --> 28:26.460
that we can grab onto
in this lifetime

28:26.460 --> 28:28.040
is a moment worth having,

28:28.040 --> 28:30.420
regardless of what
anyone else thinks.

28:30.420 --> 28:32.960
And just for the record,
you judgmental jackass,

28:32.960 --> 28:34.120
I cheated on Nathan first!

28:53.000 --> 28:55.500
[ Helicopter blades whirring ]

29:05.880 --> 29:07.080
Hey.

29:17.250 --> 29:20.120
What's wrong?
I'm sorry. I, um...

29:22.000 --> 29:23.000
I need
that necklace back.

29:26.920 --> 29:29.120
Damn it. Damn it!

29:29.120 --> 29:30.920
Just hear me out.
Okay, what did he say?

29:30.920 --> 29:33.080
No. You know what?
It doesn't matter.

29:33.080 --> 29:34.710
It was a drunken mistake.

29:34.710 --> 29:36.420
You and I were fighting,
and I was gonna tell you --

29:36.420 --> 29:38.420
Whoa, whoa. Hang on a second.
What are you saying?

29:38.420 --> 29:40.210
W-What do you think
I'm saying?

29:40.210 --> 29:42.420
Well, it sounds like
you slept with someone.

29:42.420 --> 29:43.750
Isn't that why you want
the necklace back?

29:43.750 --> 29:45.750
No! It...

29:45.750 --> 29:47.750
Then what?

29:51.880 --> 29:53.790
W-Wasn't mine to give.

29:57.830 --> 30:00.710
[ Laughs ]

30:00.710 --> 30:04.330
You proposed to me with
some other chick's necklace?!

30:06.830 --> 30:08.920
God, Nathan!
What is wrong with you?!

30:08.920 --> 30:11.420
Okay, you're not the
only one that gets to
be mad right now, okay?

30:11.420 --> 30:13.380
You cheated, too.
You just said.

30:13.380 --> 30:15.920
I know what I said.
[ Sighs ]

30:15.920 --> 30:18.000
I have been showing
that thing off all day.

30:18.000 --> 30:20.790
This is so humiliating.

30:20.790 --> 30:22.000
Did you even mean it?

30:22.000 --> 30:24.750
Of course. Did you?

30:24.750 --> 30:27.040
Lieutenant Hunt, we're having
a problem with your patient.

30:28.670 --> 30:30.000
On my way.

30:33.670 --> 30:34.750
[ Scoffs ]

30:34.750 --> 30:37.500
[ Sana shrieking ]

30:41.120 --> 30:42.880
The chest tube started
coming out when we were
transferring her.

30:42.880 --> 30:44.250
All I have to do
is reposition it,

30:44.250 --> 30:45.710
but if we give her any more
morphine for the pain,

30:45.710 --> 30:47.000
we're gonna
have to intubate.

30:47.000 --> 30:49.460
Got it. I got it.
Sana, you can get through this.

30:49.460 --> 30:51.790
Okay? Listen to me.
I need you to breathe.

30:51.790 --> 30:54.620
[ Sobbing ]
It hurts. I can't.

30:54.620 --> 30:56.330
Focus on
something else, okay?

30:56.330 --> 30:58.330
I want you to tell me
about your neighborhood,
your family, job, kids.

30:58.330 --> 31:00.580
Do you have any kids?
Aah!

31:00.580 --> 31:02.290
Okay, I'm gonna tell you
about my family.

31:02.290 --> 31:04.120
The tall, red-headed guy
yelling at everybody?

31:04.120 --> 31:06.830
That's my brother. He drives me
crazy most of the time.

31:06.830 --> 31:08.290
No, all of the time.

31:08.290 --> 31:09.460
[ Laughs lightly ]

31:09.460 --> 31:12.830
That sounds like my brother.
Yeah?

31:12.830 --> 31:15.710
He is my heart.
He means well.

31:15.710 --> 31:17.790
Yeah.

31:17.790 --> 31:19.790
[ Gasps ]

31:19.790 --> 31:21.500
[ Breathing slows ]

31:21.500 --> 31:23.880
Yeah. Mine too.

31:29.750 --> 31:31.040
Let's get her
on the next chopper!

31:31.040 --> 31:32.250
Man: I'm on it!

31:34.040 --> 31:36.710
Owen: Major Hunt.
Megan: Hi. It's me.

31:36.710 --> 31:38.830
I need to ride back
on the medical chopper.

31:38.830 --> 31:40.000
My patient's
freaking out.

31:40.000 --> 31:41.290
Well, you know
that's against protocol.

31:41.290 --> 31:42.960
And...

31:42.960 --> 31:44.330
[Voice breaking]
Nathan cheated on me.

31:44.330 --> 31:46.540
He what?

31:46.540 --> 31:48.750
So I really don't want
to have to ride back with him,

31:48.750 --> 31:50.250
but if i-it's
against protocol...

31:50.250 --> 31:52.460
Screw protocol.
Get on the chopper.

31:52.460 --> 31:55.170
Are you sure?
It's my call, and I'm sure.
That son of a bitch.

31:56.670 --> 31:59.170
Okay. [ Sniffles ]
Thanks, Owen.

32:01.210 --> 32:03.250
[ Man groans ]

32:03.250 --> 32:04.670
How you feeling?

32:04.670 --> 32:07.460
Like a truck hit me.

32:07.460 --> 32:09.670
But happy to be alive,
ma'am.

32:09.670 --> 32:12.580
I wonder if they'll electrocute
him here or fly him back home.

32:12.580 --> 32:14.540
Why are they
talking that way?

32:14.540 --> 32:17.580
He was the second shooter.
They're pretty upset.

32:17.580 --> 32:19.830
No, he wasn't. Second shooter
was an Iraqi woman.

32:19.830 --> 32:21.120
This guy was trying
to stop her.

32:25.620 --> 32:28.420
[ Helicopter blades whirring ]

32:34.620 --> 32:38.080
It's all good.
You're gonna be okay.

32:44.420 --> 32:47.710
Teddy: Megan! Megan!

32:47.710 --> 32:50.290
Megan! Stop!

32:50.290 --> 32:53.170
Stop! Megan!!

32:53.170 --> 32:54.620
Stop it!

32:54.620 --> 33:01.210
♪♪

33:01.210 --> 33:04.210
Teddy: [ Breaking up ]
Eagle 2, return...base.

33:07.170 --> 33:09.210
[ Radio static crackles ]

33:11.040 --> 33:12.880
Repeat!

33:12.880 --> 33:15.580
Eagle 2,
return to base immediately!

33:24.620 --> 33:26.290
[ Scoffs ]

33:26.290 --> 33:30.080
Riggs never said anything.
All this time.

33:30.080 --> 33:32.620
Yeah. Well...

33:32.620 --> 33:35.290
he's a good guy.

33:35.290 --> 33:37.120
Yeah.

33:40.080 --> 33:42.120
You remember
that family trip we took,

33:42.120 --> 33:44.210
somewhere in California,

33:44.210 --> 33:46.710
when I left the map
at the rest-stop bathroom?

33:46.710 --> 33:48.620
Oh, yeah. Yeah.
How could I forget?

33:48.620 --> 33:50.500
Dad was furious.
[ Chuckles ]

33:50.500 --> 33:52.540
And he refused to pull over
and ask for directions.

33:52.540 --> 33:54.380
Yep.

33:54.380 --> 33:58.120
And after him and Mom arguing
for hours and us complaining,

33:58.120 --> 34:00.460
he finally said,
"Screw it!"

34:00.460 --> 34:03.250
[Laughing] And he just,
like, pulled over.

34:03.250 --> 34:06.670
And we played in the water for
hours until the sun went down.

34:06.670 --> 34:08.000
I don't even remember
where we were going,

34:08.000 --> 34:11.170
but I just...

34:11.170 --> 34:13.920
I've never forgotten
that beach.

34:13.920 --> 34:17.420
[ Sea gulls cry ]

34:17.420 --> 34:21.540
On my hardest days, I would
lose myself in that memory.

34:21.540 --> 34:25.750
Pretend that the desert sand
was the beach,

34:25.750 --> 34:30.170
that the screams and yelling
were laughter and sea gulls.

34:30.170 --> 34:33.580
And I could fake everything
but the water.

34:33.580 --> 34:37.170
And I promised myself,
if I ever get out...

34:39.500 --> 34:43.750
...I am going to live
by the ocean, in California,

34:43.750 --> 34:47.170
and I'm gonna feel
that water every day.

34:52.750 --> 34:54.170
[ Exhales deeply ]

34:54.170 --> 34:58.460
I always imagined us raising our
families together, you know?

34:58.460 --> 35:02.120
Next door, or a few blocks,
near Mom and Dad.

35:04.460 --> 35:06.790
Camping trips
and cookouts.

35:08.670 --> 35:12.000
Dad's gone, Owen.

35:12.000 --> 35:15.290
And you don't have
any kids.

35:15.290 --> 35:17.210
How exactly would
that dream work out?

35:17.210 --> 35:20.540
[ Chuckles ]

35:20.540 --> 35:24.420
You are the most loyal person
I have ever known.

35:24.420 --> 35:26.380
But you're loyal
to ideas, too.

35:26.380 --> 35:28.540
Ideas and ideals.

35:31.080 --> 35:33.880
My beach plan
makes me happy.

35:33.880 --> 35:36.460
Like, "I can feel it
in my fingers" happy.

35:36.460 --> 35:40.040
I want that for you.
I want to see you happy.

35:40.040 --> 35:42.290
And that might mean that
you're gonna have to break up

35:42.290 --> 35:43.620
with some of your ideals.

35:45.750 --> 35:53.380
♪♪

35:53.380 --> 35:55.670
Yeah.

35:55.670 --> 36:00.620
♪♪

36:00.620 --> 36:05.960
♪♪

36:05.960 --> 36:08.380
♪ Hanging by a thread ♪

36:08.380 --> 36:13.290
♪ Waiting for a hand
to pull me up ♪

36:13.290 --> 36:16.960
[ Cellphone clicking ]

36:16.960 --> 36:19.420
♪ Falling down instead ♪

36:19.420 --> 36:21.830
♪ Nowhere left to land ♪
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

36:21.830 --> 36:24.540
♪ It's all you get ♪

36:27.170 --> 36:30.790
♪ For holding on ♪

36:32.960 --> 36:37.790
♪ To something
that will never come ♪

36:37.790 --> 36:41.290
♪ Am I holding on ♪

36:41.290 --> 36:43.580
[ Sighs ]

36:43.580 --> 36:47.380
♪ To something
that will never come? ♪

36:49.580 --> 36:54.330
♪ I don't have
enough heartbeats left ♪

36:54.330 --> 36:57.330
♪ To spare them on somebody ♪

36:57.330 --> 37:00.210
♪ Spare them on somebody ♪

37:00.210 --> 37:04.920
♪ Who never planned
to see the moments pass ♪

37:04.920 --> 37:06.960
I...

37:06.960 --> 37:09.710
was promised
move-in ready.

37:09.710 --> 37:13.290
[ Light laughter ]

37:13.290 --> 37:16.250
Mm.
Mm. [ Chuckles ]

37:16.250 --> 37:17.920
[ Whispering ] Hey.
[ Whispering ] Hi.

37:19.880 --> 37:22.620
Welcome home.
Oh.

37:25.000 --> 37:28.830
♪ Footprints in the sand
remind us that we can ♪

37:28.830 --> 37:30.420
How was your day?

37:30.420 --> 37:32.750
Yeah, it was --
It was pretty okay.

37:32.750 --> 37:34.040
Yeah?
Mm-hmm.

37:34.040 --> 37:37.040
You raised a great kid.

37:37.040 --> 37:38.500
♪ Light, it turns to dust ♪

37:38.500 --> 37:40.000
♪ And leaves because
it must evaporate ♪

37:40.000 --> 37:42.670
Thanks. [ Laughs ]

37:42.670 --> 37:46.290
Where's Owen?

37:46.290 --> 37:49.040
I dropped him off
at the airport.

37:49.040 --> 37:51.710
He said
he'll come visit soon.

37:51.710 --> 37:56.880
♪ To something
that's already gone ♪

37:56.880 --> 38:00.710
♪ Am I holding on ♪

38:00.710 --> 38:02.790
[ Sighs ]

38:02.790 --> 38:08.540
♪ To something
that's already gone? ♪

38:08.540 --> 38:13.460
♪ I don't have
enough heartbeats left ♪

38:13.460 --> 38:16.790
♪ To spare them on somebody ♪

38:16.790 --> 38:20.920
♪ Spare them on somebody
who never planned to see ♪

38:20.920 --> 38:23.250
Owen: When we've come
to depend on a cycle,

38:23.250 --> 38:25.250
the thought of breaking it
is scary.

38:25.250 --> 38:27.500
♪ Now until forever ♪

38:27.500 --> 38:32.170
♪ Now until our last breath ♪

38:32.170 --> 38:35.880
♪ Now until our last breath ♪

38:37.750 --> 38:39.040
-Hey.
-Hey.

38:39.040 --> 38:41.880
-You're back.
-Yeah.

38:46.460 --> 38:48.420
Even the cycles
that cause us harm.

38:48.420 --> 38:50.580
Oh.

38:53.330 --> 38:55.040
Amelia, I'm so sorry.

38:56.790 --> 38:59.040
You married a tumor.

38:59.040 --> 39:00.710
I get it.

39:00.710 --> 39:02.960
It just...

39:04.670 --> 39:06.670
It feels like
we don't know each other.

39:08.620 --> 39:10.790
Yeah, I know.

39:10.790 --> 39:13.120
I just want us
to be happy.

39:13.120 --> 39:15.210
And we're --
We're not happy.

39:18.290 --> 39:20.170
I know.

39:23.670 --> 39:25.120
It's okay, Owen.

39:28.500 --> 39:30.250
I know.

39:54.580 --> 39:57.920
But sometimes,
when we break the cycle...

39:57.920 --> 39:59.000
♪ Da-da, da-da-da ♪

39:59.000 --> 40:01.420
♪ Da, da-da-da, da, da ♪

40:03.380 --> 40:05.080
♪ Da-da, da-da-da ♪

40:05.080 --> 40:08.040
♪ Da, da-da-da, da, da ♪

40:08.040 --> 40:09.750
...we find something better.

40:09.750 --> 40:11.710
♪ Da-da, da-da-da ♪

40:11.710 --> 40:14.460
Something unexpected.

40:14.460 --> 40:16.420
♪ Da-da, da-da-da ♪

40:16.420 --> 40:20.250
♪ Da, da-da-da, da, da ♪

40:20.250 --> 40:22.750
♪ Da-da, da-da-da ♪

40:22.750 --> 40:24.790
Something we never dared
to dream was possible.

40:24.790 --> 40:26.750
♪ Da-da, da-da-da ♪

40:26.750 --> 40:29.920
[ Sobbing, laughing ]

40:29.920 --> 40:33.830
♪ Da-da, da-da-da ♪

40:33.830 --> 40:35.710
Megan: Aah!

40:35.710 --> 40:37.830
♪ Da-da, da-da-da ♪

40:37.830 --> 40:40.670
[ Laughter ]

40:42.460 --> 40:44.380
-Get her!
-Aah!

40:44.380 --> 40:46.790
♪ Ah-ah ♪

40:46.790 --> 40:49.960
♪ Ohh-ohh-oh ♪

40:49.960 --> 40:51.920
We find freedom.

40:51.920 --> 40:55.580
♪ Ohh-ahh ♪

40:55.580 --> 40:57.750
♪ Ohh ♪

40:57.750 --> 41:00.540
♪ Ahh-ohh ♪

41:00.540 --> 41:02.210
♪ Ohh-ohh ♪

41:02.210 --> 41:07.540
♪♪

41:07.540 --> 41:09.580
[ Sea gulls cry ]

41:09.580 --> 41:13.920
♪♪

41:13.920 --> 41:16.460
We find peace.

41:16.460 --> 41:18.500
[ Breathes deeply ]

41:28.170 --> 41:36.330
♪♪

41:36.330 --> 41:44.790
♪♪

41:44.790 --> 41:53.000
♪♪
